        "type": "text",
        "text": "---\n\n## **Updated NDA Triage — Four New Additions**\n\n| # | Counterparty | Verdict | Top Issues | Action |\n|---|---|---|---|---|\n| 7 | GreenLine ERP Systems | **RED** | Perpetual term, no residuals, non-compete clause, $500k liquidated damages, Texas exclusive jurisdiction | **Do not sign.** Escalate to GC. This is a one-way NDA with multiple deal-breaker terms |\n| 8 | Harborwave Cloud Services | **GREEN** | None; includes GDPR trigger for separate DPA (appropriate) | Sign as drafted |\n| 9 | Iris Consulting Group | **YELLOW** | 10-year survival (excessive), non-solicitation clause (reasonable scope) | Legal review; push survival to 3+3 (max 6 years total), clarify non-solicitation language |\n| 10 | Jadestone Manufacturing | **GREEN** | None | Sign as drafted |\n\n---\n\n## **Detail on New YELLOW and RED Items**\n\n### **GreenLine ERP Systems — RED**\n\nThis is a one-way NDA running to Stanford with multiple deal-breaker clauses. **Do not sign without GC engagement.**\n\n**Issue 1: Perpetual term.** Section 3 states obligations \"survive in perpetuity…There is no termination date and the obligations do not lapse.\" Red flag per playbook.\n\n**Issue 2: No residuals carve-out.** Section 4 explicitly prohibits the standard residuals exception. Requires personnel to treat residual memory as bound indefinitely — operationally unworkable and legally unusual.\n\n**Issue 3: Non-compete clause.** Section 5 prohibits Stanford from engaging \"any third-party supplier of ERP services that competes with GreenLine in respect of any line of business in which GreenLine has disclosed Confidential Information\" for 2 years post-discussions. This is a non-compete disguised as an NDA term — it goes far beyond protecting confidential information and restricts Stanford's freedom to procure. Red flag per playbook.\n\n**Issue 4: Liquidated damages.** Section 6 sets liquidated damages at US$500,000 per incident of breach. GreenLine has pre-calculated the penalty for alleged breaches; this signals litigation intent. Red flag per playbook.\n\n**Issue 5: Forum and governing law.** Texas law + exclusive jurisdiction + \"without regard to conflict-of-laws principles\" (conflict-waiver language sometimes used for forum-shopping). Adds cost-of-litigation risk.\n\n**Recommendation:** Route to GC with a summary memo. If GreenLine's ERP services are strategic, GC should engage their legal team directly to reframe the discussion (separate the non-compete into a separate agreement, kill the LD clause, move to mutual 2+3 term, and add residuals carve-out). This is not a one-round redline.\n\n---\n\n### **Iris Consulting Group — YELLOW**\n\n**Issue 1: Extended survival.** Section 4 gives 3-year operative term + 10-year survival *from date of disclosure* (rolling). This means confidential information disclosed on day 1 of year 3 would survive 10 additional years (13 years total from execution). This is well beyond the playbook threshold of 7 years total. ESG consulting is not trade-secret work justifying a 13-year tail. **Redline:** push to 3-year operative + 3-year survival from *date of disclosure* (max 6 years total), or alternatively 3-year operative + 3-year survival from *termination* of the Agreement (simpler administration).\n\n**Issue 2: Non-solicitation clause.** Section 5 restricts solicitation of \"any employee of the other party with whom it has had contact during the Purpose\" for 12 months post-termination. Scope is reasonable (actual contact, limited duration), but the language \"with whom it has had contact\" is fact-sensitive. **Redline:** for clarity, add \"directly or in connection with the Purpose\" so the clause does not sweep in employees merely present in meetings.\n\n---\n\n## **Revised Full Batch Summary (10 NDAs)**\n\n**GREEN (sign immediately): 5**\n- ACME Tooling Solutions\n- Delphi Components\n- Folium Research Institute\n- Harborwave Cloud Services\n- Jadestone Manufacturing\n\n**YELLOW (legal review + redline): 3**\n- BetaCorp Logistics\n- Emberlake Holdings\n- Iris Consulting Group\n\n**RED (escalate to GC): 2**\n- Cypress Systems\n- GreenLine ERP Systems"
      }
